body:
On EuroPython we sprinted on making Cython single-source compatible between py2/py3, because waiting for the 2to3 run each time a change needs to be tested takes an annoying amount of time.

The shrinking list of 2to3 fixers that are still needed is in 2to3-fixers.txt.

commit.message: Use an explicit list of 2to3 fixers
fix missing exception type in setup.py
make raw_input() usage compatible with Py2/Py3
adapt usages of map() to Py2/Py3
Adapt StringIO & buildins imports to Py2/Py3
Convert xrange uses to range/enumerate/list(range()) for Py2/Py3 compatibility

title: (WIP) Get rid of 2to3
